This is present when groups discuss how well they are achieving their goals and how to maintain effective working relationships.

“We know what skills will help us communicate and succeed in school and life!”



reflexão do grupo;
avaliação de funcionamento;
manutenção de relações eficazes.


Part of Active Methodologies for Teaching and Learning. LearningLandscapes

The group is responsible for achieving its goals and each member is responsible for his or her share of the work.

“We’re accountable to somebody for our thinking and contributions.”



responsabilidade individual;
responsabilidade coletiva;
cada membro contribui.


Part of Active Methodologies for Teaching and Learning. LearningLandscapes

This exists when students perceive they are linked with each other in a way that one cannot succeed unless everyone succeeds. If one fails, they all fail. It creates commitment and is at the heart of Cooperative Learning.

“We need each other to succeed.”



ninguém tem sucesso sozinho;
se um falha, todos falham;
compromisso coletivo.


Part of Active Methodologies for Teaching and Learning. LearningLandscapes

This occurs when members share resources and encourage, help and praise each other’s efforts to learn.
Cooperative groups are both an academic and personal support system.

“Everyone has the chance to participate something valuable.”



partilha;
apoio;
encorajamento;
praise;
ajuda mútua.


Part of Active Methodologies for Teaching and Learning. LearningLandscapes

Group members must know how to provide effective leadership, decision-making, trust-building, communication and conflict management.
Teachers must teach teamwork skills just as they do academic skills.

“We’re always moving around and working with people that are different from us.”


Necessidade de ensinar:

leadership;
decision-making;
trust-building;
communication;
conflict management.


